1
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:54,172
[ GRUNTS ]

2
00:02:04,016 --> 00:02:05,350
MAN:
Psst.

3
00:02:30,334 --> 00:02:31,417
LEE [ IN CHINESE ]:

4
00:02:57,194 --> 00:02:58,695
[ GRUNTING ]

5
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:05,576
[ SANG SHOUTS IN CHINESE ]

6
00:03:06,078 --> 00:03:07,203
[ SPEAKS IN CHINESE ]

7
00:03:10,749 --> 00:03:12,542
[ GUNSHOTS ]

8
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:14,585
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

9
00:03:35,274 --> 00:03:37,525
[ GRUNTING ]

10
00:03:41,572 --> 00:03:43,573
[ BOAT ENGINE CHUGGING ]

11
00:04:02,426 --> 00:04:05,052
MAN:
Forgive me, Consul Han...

12
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:09,849
...but I believe we can ill afford
to lose men of your high character.

13
00:04:10,017 --> 00:04:12,143
And speaking as a friend...

14
00:04:12,311 --> 00:04:15,772
...who's fought side by side
with you for 15 years...

15
00:04:15,939 --> 00:04:18,232
...I will sorely miss
the unshakable support...

16
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,359
...you've given
the Royal Hong Kong Police.

17
00:04:20,527 --> 00:04:23,571
And so on behalf of all Brits...

18
00:04:23,739 --> 00:04:27,241
...who have ever carried the shield
in Hong Kong, we shall miss you.

19
00:04:27,409 --> 00:04:28,826
We wish you happiness...

20
00:04:28,994 --> 00:04:31,454
...as you take up your new post
in the United States.

21
00:04:31,622 --> 00:04:34,415
Ladies and gentlemen, Consul Han.

22
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:35,792
GUESTS:
Consul Han.

23
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:37,752
HAN:
Thank you, Thomas.

24
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:45,009
Now, you know Thomas is not going
to make this evening easy.

25
00:04:45,177 --> 00:04:46,552
[ IN ENGLISH ]
Excuse me.

26
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,805
[ WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY ]

27
00:04:50,766 --> 00:04:52,099
[ SPEAKS IN CHINESE ]

28
00:04:53,227 --> 00:04:54,310
Commander Griffin...

29
00:04:54,478 --> 00:04:57,104
...I am pleased to be able
to leave you and Hong Kong...

30
00:04:57,272 --> 00:04:59,315
...with a special gift tonight.

31
00:04:59,483 --> 00:05:01,818
Earlier this evening,
Detective Inspector Lee...

32
00:05:01,985 --> 00:05:04,821
...and his special task force
have once and for all...

33
00:05:04,988 --> 00:05:08,449
...crushed the Juntao criminal
organization and reclaimed artifacts...

34
00:05:08,617 --> 00:05:11,035
...from 5000 years of China's heritage.

35
00:05:14,331 --> 00:05:15,665
[ SPEAKS IN CHINESE ]

36
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:19,210
This is the kind of legacy I dreamt about.

37
00:05:20,295 --> 00:05:21,462
Hong Kong forever.

38
00:05:22,005 --> 00:05:24,006
To Hong Kong forever.

39
00:05:24,341 --> 00:05:26,968
GUESTS:
Hong Kong forever.

40
00:05:29,847 --> 00:05:31,180
[ GRUNTS ]

41
00:05:31,598 --> 00:05:32,640
Soo Yung.

42
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:34,851
[ IN CHINESE ]

43
00:05:35,352 --> 00:05:36,352
[ IN CHINESE ]

44
00:06:10,971 --> 00:06:12,013
[ CAR HORN HONKS ]

45
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:14,432
MAN 1:
Stupid fool! Get the hell out of my way!

46
00:06:14,725 --> 00:06:16,559
Man, are you crazy?

47
00:06:16,727 --> 00:06:19,395
-Shoot!
MAN 2: You moron!

48
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,570
Clive, what's up, man?

49
00:06:27,738 --> 00:06:29,071
-You're late.
-Huh?

50
00:06:29,239 --> 00:06:30,364
You're late.

51
00:06:30,532 --> 00:06:31,908
-I'm late?
-Yeah, you're late.

52
00:06:32,075 --> 00:06:35,161
You're late, man. I've been waiting
in the back for over an hour.

53
00:06:35,329 --> 00:06:37,705
-I was in the diner.
-Man, I told you in the back.

54
00:06:37,873 --> 00:06:39,749
Think I would do this shit out front?

55
00:06:39,917 --> 00:06:42,418
-I'm gonna get busted.
-You weren't in the diner.

56
00:06:42,586 --> 00:06:45,087
I said in the back of the d―
It don't even matter.

57
00:06:45,255 --> 00:06:47,924
I'm late, you late. Let's do this.
What's that, a gun?

58
00:06:48,091 --> 00:06:50,509
Put that away.
How many people you killed this year?

59
00:06:50,677 --> 00:06:53,930
-Stop it, man. Let's do it. Come on.
-Don't be late again.

60
00:06:54,097 --> 00:06:56,307
I ain't gonna be late. Come on.
What we got?

61
00:06:56,892 --> 00:06:58,267
Hoo-hoo.

62
00:06:58,435 --> 00:07:02,480
That's tight. That's beautiful.
That's nice. What's that?

63
00:07:02,648 --> 00:07:04,565
-That's C-4.
-That's C-4?

64
00:07:04,733 --> 00:07:05,775
That's C-4.

65
00:07:05,943 --> 00:07:08,277
-Oh, shit.
-What's the problem?

66
00:07:08,445 --> 00:07:10,863
No problem. I been looking
everywhere for this shit.

67
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:12,782
Man, how the hell you find some C-4?

68
00:07:12,950 --> 00:07:17,078
You don't know how you make me feel,
man. The Iraqis can't even get this shit.

69
00:07:17,245 --> 00:07:19,580
-Where'd you get this from?
-It's a hot ticket.

70
00:07:19,957 --> 00:07:21,666
CARTER: You don't know how happy
you made me.

71
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,335
You got what I want.
Let me go get that money, man.

72
00:07:24,503 --> 00:07:26,253
Step away from the car.

73
00:07:26,421 --> 00:07:27,755
Hey, officers.

74
00:07:27,923 --> 00:07:30,716
OFFICER: Put your hands above your heads.
Just do it now.

75
00:07:30,884 --> 00:07:33,761
CARTER: Ain't no problem here.
Why y'all messing with us for?

76
00:07:34,596 --> 00:07:35,680
All right, take it easy.

77
00:07:35,847 --> 00:07:37,556
-You don't wanna do that.
-Yes, I do.

78
00:07:37,724 --> 00:07:40,142
-No, he don't. He's playing.
-No, I ain't playing.

79
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:42,979
-Yes, he is, officer.
-No, I'm not. I'm not playing!

80
00:07:43,146 --> 00:07:45,940
-Drop the gun!
-He's just my cousin. We're just talking.

81
00:07:46,108 --> 00:07:47,525
Get back in the car and leave.

82
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:48,818
Can't do that, buddy.

83
00:07:48,986 --> 00:07:51,153
I'll blow his head all over the parking lot!

84
00:07:51,321 --> 00:07:54,490
-Get in the car and buy some doughnuts!
CARTER: See? You made him mad.

85
00:07:54,658 --> 00:07:56,283
Let me just talk to him. All right?

86
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:58,536
OFFICER 1: Hey!
OFFICER 2: Don't move!

87
00:07:58,704 --> 00:08:01,205
All right. All right. Everything cool now.

88
00:08:01,373 --> 00:08:04,500
He down. The gun down.
Now get back in the car and just leave.

89
00:08:04,668 --> 00:08:07,461
-Put your hands on your head!
-Everything's cool, officer.

90
00:08:07,629 --> 00:08:09,505
Do it now!

91
00:08:15,012 --> 00:08:16,303
OFFICER 2:
My arm!

92
00:08:28,483 --> 00:08:30,693
Didn't I tell you to get in the car?

93
00:08:33,155 --> 00:08:34,321
[ GUNSHOT ]

94
00:08:34,698 --> 00:08:36,866
[ CAR HORNS HONKING ]

95
00:08:51,173 --> 00:08:53,174
Man, stop it! I got C-4 in the trunk!

96
00:09:08,523 --> 00:09:09,982
Yeah!

97
00:09:16,948 --> 00:09:18,407
Hoo-hoo.

98
00:09:20,243 --> 00:09:22,745
Clive, guess what, man.

99
00:09:22,913 --> 00:09:25,623
I forgot to tell you. I'm L.A.P.D.

100
00:09:25,791 --> 00:09:27,583
You under arrest.

101
00:09:32,798 --> 00:09:34,924
HAN:
Soo Yung, come on, we're gonna be late.

102
00:09:35,425 --> 00:09:36,926
Let's go.

103
00:09:37,427 --> 00:09:39,095
WOMAN:
Excuse me.

104
00:09:40,138 --> 00:09:43,390
-What?
-Telephone. China.

105
00:09:43,809 --> 00:09:45,142
[ SPEAKS IN CHINESE ]

106
00:09:46,103 --> 00:09:49,313
Soo Yung, I love you. Have a nice day.

107
00:09:49,481 --> 00:09:51,107
[ IN ENGLISH ]
Will you be home after school?

108
00:09:52,275 --> 00:09:53,776
No.

109
00:09:53,944 --> 00:09:56,487
I am going to pick you up myself.

110
00:09:56,696 --> 00:09:58,322
[ SPEAKING IN CHINESE ]

111
00:10:01,326 --> 00:10:03,327
-Bye.
-Bye.

112
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,000
[ IN CHINESE ]

113
00:10:10,335 --> 00:10:11,377
[ IN ENGLISH ]
Hello?

114
00:10:11,545 --> 00:10:13,045
[ PHONE LINE CLICKS ]

115
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,839
Hello?

116
00:10:23,807 --> 00:10:25,808
[ MARIAH CAREY'S "FANTASY" PLAYING
ON RADIO ]

117
00:10:26,143 --> 00:10:28,477
[ SINGING ]
<i>Oh, when you walk by every night</i>

118
00:10:28,645 --> 00:10:30,855
<i>Talking sweet and looking fine</i>

119
00:10:31,022 --> 00:10:34,567
<i>I get kinda hectic inside</i>

